HEADWORD: Teracrylic
<hw>Ter`a*cryl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ter</ets>pene + <ets>acrylic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid of the acrylic series,
obtained by the distillation of terpenylic acid, as an only substance
having a peculiar cheesy odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

